  "dateModified": "2025-12-31",
  "datePublished": "2025-12-31",
  "description": "A sign is something that stands for something else to an interpreter — a triadic relation among representamen, object, and interpretant in Peirce's account; a dyadic relation between signifier and signified in Saussure's.",
